quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  9,46,"Had they wished to go forth, they would have prepared for it a preparation; but God was averse from their starting off, and made them halt, and they were told to sit with those who sit"
  9,47,"Had they gone forth with you they would but have made you more trouble, and they would have hurried about amongst you craving a sedition; amongst you are some who would have listened to them; but God knows those who are unjust"
  9,48,"They used to crave sedition before and upset thy affairs; until the truth came, and God's bidding was made manifest, averse although they were"
  9,49,"Of them are some who say, 'Permit me, and do not try me!' Have they not fallen into the trial already, but hell shall encompass the misbelievers"
  9,50,"If good befall thee it seems ill to them; but if a calamity befall thee they say, 'We had taken care for our affair before;' and they turn their backs and they are glad"
  9,51,"Say, 'Nought shall befall us save what God has written down for us; He is our Lord, and upon God believers do rely"
  9,52,"Say, 'Do ye await for us aught but one of the two best things?' we too await for you that God will inflict on you torment from Himself, or by our hands. Wait then; and we with you are waiting too"
  9,53,"Say, 'Expend ye in alms, whether ye will or no, it shall not be accepted from you; verily, ye are a people who do work abomination"
  9,54,"But nought hinders their alms-giving from being accepted save that they misbelieve in God and His Apostle, and perform not prayer save lazily, and expend not in alms save reluctantly"
  9,55,"Let not their wealth please you nor their children, God only wishes to torment them therewith in the life of this world, and that their souls may pass away while still they misbelieve"
  9,56,"They swear by God that, verily, they are of you; but they are not of you, and they are a people who do stand aside in fear"
  9,57,"Could they but have found a refuge, or some caves, or a place in which to creep, they would have turned round in haste thereto"
  9,58,"Of them are some who defame thee, with respect to alms; though if they are given a part thereof, they are content; and if they are not given a part thereof, then are they in a rage"
  9,59,"Would that they were content with what God and His Apostle had brought them, and would say, 'God is enough for us! God will bring us of His grace, and so will His Apostle; verily, unto God is our desire"